<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1451,597,764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,463,597,624]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Persoon" authorityYear="1806" box="[463,729,598,624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophthalmica">
<emphasis box="[463,729,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Euphorbia ophthalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a worldwide tropical and subtropical weed. In the State of 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
the species is very common, mainly on disturbed areas.
</paragraph>
