<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1451,597,764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,430,701,728]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Persoon" authorityYear="1806" box="[430,699,702,728]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophthalmica">
<emphasis box="[430,699,702,728]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Euphorbia ophthalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[914,1001,702,728]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[914,1001,702,728]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">E. hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the cyathia arranged in capitate synflorescences, but the species differ, mainly, on the position of them (see notes under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1119,1300,738,764]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[1119,1300,738,764]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Euphorbia hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
